  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into large pieces</p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 25-30 min or until everything is cooked through and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> chives</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped chives</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of <strong>water</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> chive dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have had an initial 25-30 min, remove the tray from the oven and add your <strong>meat-free bacon lardons</strong> and the <strong>sliced spring greens </strong>and<strong> </strong>stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 7 min or until the spring greens have wilted and the meat-free bacon<strong> </strong>is warmed through – this is your <strong>roasted pepper & plant-based bacon tray bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-plant-based-bacon-herby-tray-bake/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted pepper & plant-based bacon tray bake</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>chive dressing</strong> all over and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
